The global hemp seed market is segmented based on type, application, and distribution channels. Under the type segment, the market is divided into conventional hemp seeds and organic hemp seeds. Organic hemp seeds are witnessing a surge in demand due to the increasing health consciousness among consumers and the growing trend of organic products. In terms of applications, hemp seeds are used in various industries such as food & beverages, personal care products, pharma & nutraceuticals, and others. The food & beverages segment dominates the market due to the high nutritional value and versatility of hemp seeds in food products. When it comes to distribution channels, the market is fragmented into hypermarkets/supermarkets, convenience stores, online retail, and others. The online retail segment is experiencing significant growth, driven by the convenience and wide product variety offered to consumers.

