In terms of applications, the food & beverages segment is the largest consumer of hemp seeds, owing to their rich nutritional profile and versatility in various culinary creations. Hemp seeds are sought after for their high protein content, essential fatty acids, and minerals, making them a popular choice among health-conscious consumers and athletes. Moreover, the increasing use of hemp seeds in personal care products and the pharmaceutical industry is creating new opportunities for market growth. Hemp-derived products are valued for their potential health benefits, including anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, driving their utilization in skincare formulations and nutraceutical supplements.

When it comes to distribution channels, the online retail segment is experiencing rapid growth, supported by the expanding e-commerce platforms and the convenience of doorstep delivery. Consumers are increasingly turning to online channels to purchase hemp seed products due to the wider product selection, promotional offers, and easy access to product information. Hypermarkets/supermarkets and convenience stores also play a crucial role in the market, providing essential visibility to hemp seed products and catering to the impulse purchase behavior of shoppers. Diversifying distribution channels and enhancing product availability will be key strategies for market players to reach a broader consumer base and drive sales growth.

